## 1. Purpose

This AI Risk Register provides a structured, living record of all identified risks associated with {{ business_name }}'s use of artificial intelligence. It supports compliance with:

- **AI6 Essential Practice 3** — Manage Risks
- **Privacy Act 1988** — Risk-based approach to privacy compliance
- **OAIC AI Guidance (October 2024)** — Expectation of documented AI risk management
- **POLA Act 2024** — Transparency in automated decision-making

This register must be reviewed quarterly and updated whenever new AI tools are deployed, existing tools are modified, or new risks are identified.

## 2. Risk Assessment Methodology

### 2.1 Likelihood Scale

| Rating | Score | Description |
|---|---|---|
| Rare | 1 | May occur in exceptional circumstances |
| Unlikely | 2 | Could occur but not expected |
| Possible | 3 | Might occur at some time |
| Likely | 4 | Will probably occur in most circumstances |
| Almost Certain | 5 | Expected to occur in most circumstances |

### 2.2 Impact Scale

| Rating | Score | Description |
|---|---|---|
| Insignificant | 1 | Minimal impact, easily managed |
| Minor | 2 | Some impact, manageable with existing controls |
| Moderate | 3 | Significant impact, requires management attention |
| Major | 4 | Serious impact, potential regulatory consequences |
| Catastrophic | 5 | Critical impact, existential threat or major regulatory penalty |

### 2.3 Risk Rating Matrix

| | Insignificant (1) | Minor (2) | Moderate (3) | Major (4) | Catastrophic (5) |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Almost Certain (5) | Medium | High | High | Extreme | Extreme |
| Likely (4) | Low | Medium | High | High | Extreme |
| Possible (3) | Low | Medium | Medium | High | High |
| Unlikely (2) | Low | Low | Medium | Medium | High |
| Rare (1) | Low | Low | Low | Medium | Medium |

